external_knowledge:
- "more seasoned than the average coach" refers to coaches whose years of experience are greater than the average years of experience across all coaches;
- "most prestigious certification" refers to the certification level of the coach with the highest years of experience;
- "team size exceeds the average team size" means the team has more athletes than the average team size.

sql:
SELECT T.team_size, C.coach_name 
FROM teams AS T 
JOIN coaches AS C ON T.team_id = C.team_id;

external_knowledge:
- `event_id = 1` refers to the first event in the competition;
- "Valiant contenders" metaphorically refers to the athletes;
- "Grand arena of competition" metaphorically refers to the venue or setting of the event.

- 'Top 3 performers' refers to the athletes with the highest result points for each event type;
- 'Event type' includes various athletic events such as 100m Dash, Long Jump, etc.;
- 'Total athletes' in a team refers to the count of unique athletes associated with that team.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT r.athlete_id) AS number_of_wins
FROM results r
WHERE r.result_rank = 1;

